detail_description: Located in Ratnagiri, Maharashtra, India, the Ratnagiri Marine Fish Museum, also known as the Marine Biological Research Station Museum, was established in 1985. The museum offers visitors the opportunity to explore the biodiversity of the Arabian Sea through preserved specimens and live exhibits.

excerpt: Imposing 1670 stone fortress built atop a hill, also featuring a temple & nearby lighthouse.
detail_description: Nestled atop a hill and overlooking the Arabian Sea, Ratnadurga Fort is an impressive stone fortress built in 1670. Although it has seen better days, its remnants still tell tales of history while offering breathtaking views of sunsets over the sea.
